00:43:10.901 --> 00:43:12.819
He really became a Doctor.

00:43:24.420 --> 00:43:25.421
Carmela!

00:43:32.689 --> 00:43:34.114
I just want to apologize

00:43:34.139 --> 00:43:36.620
for all the wrong things
I've done to you.

00:43:37.897 --> 00:43:40.107
I also want to apologize
for being so shallow.

00:43:42.667 --> 00:43:44.293
It's not too late for us, right?

00:43:44.440 --> 00:43:45.440
Beshie?

00:43:45.733 --> 00:43:46.733
Of course.

00:43:47.402 --> 00:43:48.402
Beshie.

00:44:00.832 --> 00:44:01.832
Hello?

00:44:03.501 --> 00:44:04.544
Good day to you.

00:44:04.569 --> 00:44:05.755
Please come in.

00:44:06.434 --> 00:44:07.434
What can I help you with?

00:45:08.149 --> 00:45:09.275
I'll go ahead.

00:45:10.526 --> 00:45:11.526
Wait...

00:45:13.529 --> 00:45:14.529
I think...

00:45:14.948 --> 00:45:15.949
I already saw you.

00:45:17.450 --> 00:45:18.450
What?

00:45:20.161 --> 00:45:21.161
That's right.

00:45:22.747 --> 00:45:23.747
It's you.

00:45:25.375 --> 00:45:27.085
You're the one in the painting.

00:45:29.379 --> 00:45:30.379
Painting?

00:45:58.491 --> 00:45:59.826
He finished it.

00:46:00.488 --> 00:46:01.488
They said,

00:46:01.869 --> 00:46:04.272
Don Juanito didn't get
the chance to get married.

00:46:04.414 --> 00:46:07.598
Because he was devastated
waiting for a girl she truly loves.

00:46:08.617 --> 00:46:10.369
He loved that woman very much.

00:46:13.826 --> 00:46:15.661
Every day, before twilight,

00:46:16.538 --> 00:46:19.541
he will always be at the
mango tree outside the hacienda.

00:46:20.004 --> 00:46:21.964
To wait for the woman's return.

00:46:25.643 --> 00:46:27.528
But the days passed...

00:46:27.553 --> 00:46:28.638
The months...

00:46:28.817 --> 00:46:31.923
The years... And even
after decades until his death.

00:46:32.259 --> 00:46:33.787
The woman never returned.

00:46:36.328 --> 00:46:38.203
This woman, they called her...

00:46:39.014 --> 00:46:40.974
Carmelita Montecarlos.

00:46:41.821 --> 00:46:43.235
But this woman in the portrait was named..

00:46:43.330 --> 00:46:44.665
Carmela Isabella.

00:46:44.690 --> 00:46:45.850
By great-grandfather Juanito.

00:47:10.254 --> 00:47:11.272
Aside from that,

00:47:11.272 --> 00:47:13.192
my great-grandfather
Juanito left another thing.

00:47:15.610 --> 00:47:17.070
These are the diaries.

00:47:49.394 --> 00:47:50.394
Child,

00:47:51.187 --> 00:47:52.563
are you alright?

00:47:55.441 --> 00:47:58.694
Why do you seem so lost
in thought sometimes?

00:47:59.529 --> 00:48:01.906
Your father is getting worried.

00:48:04.117 --> 00:48:07.078
You've been here in
San Alfonso for three weeks.

00:48:08.704 --> 00:48:10.123
Is there a problem?

00:48:11.374 --> 00:48:13.876
On your birthday,

00:48:15.169 --> 00:48:17.422
I should've given this to you.

00:48:18.548 --> 00:48:20.758
But you went home immediately.

00:48:22.366 --> 00:48:26.620
Good thing I found it
while cleaning the room.

00:48:37.608 --> 00:48:39.360
And that letter

00:48:41.487 --> 00:48:42.864
was from...

00:48:44.198 --> 00:48:46.909
Mr. Juanito.

00:48:57.628 --> 00:49:00.047
I have only seen it once.

00:49:18.483 --> 00:49:20.026
Please put it inside the library.

00:49:20.051 --> 00:49:21.051
Thank you!

00:49:22.408 --> 00:49:23.408
Um...

00:49:23.633 --> 00:49:26.093
Sir, when will the paints arrive?

00:49:26.132 --> 00:49:27.381
It's on its way, ma'am.

00:49:27.406 --> 00:49:28.406
Oh, alright then.

00:49:32.580 --> 00:49:34.081
Hello, Emily?

00:49:34.624 --> 00:49:36.744
Carmela, Dad and I we're on our way.

00:49:36.918 --> 00:49:41.022
We just need the papers so you
can open your new museum next month.

00:49:41.099 --> 00:49:42.475
- Really?
- Yeah.

00:49:42.590 --> 00:49:45.234
Dad's really on full support
even though you shifted course.

00:49:45.551 --> 00:49:46.860
Even Grandmother Carmina.

00:49:47.195 --> 00:49:49.363
I think they are happy that
you already found your passion.

00:49:49.388 --> 00:49:50.389
Which is history.

00:49:52.475 --> 00:49:54.060
This isn't just for me.

00:49:54.473 --> 00:49:56.684
This museum will also be a great help

00:49:56.871 --> 00:49:59.415
to preserve the history of San Alfonso.

00:50:00.066 --> 00:50:01.609
Emily, I'll go ahead, okay?

00:50:01.802 --> 00:50:02.802
Alright.

00:50:08.658 --> 00:50:12.453
- Sir, let's follow up. Thank you.
- Yes, ma'am. No problem.

00:50:16.015 --> 00:50:18.392
- Ma'am?
- Yes, what is it, Lorenzo?

00:50:18.417 --> 00:50:20.211
Where do you want to put this painting?

00:50:20.260 --> 00:50:22.188
Maybe upstairs.

00:50:22.213 --> 00:50:23.881
At the right wing, second slot.

00:50:23.881 --> 00:50:25.174
- I got it.
- Alright.

00:50:25.788 --> 00:50:27.373
That painting is truly remarkable.

00:50:30.096 --> 00:50:31.597
Go ahead. Alright.

00:50:33.182 --> 00:50:34.350
That's why you look so familiar.

00:50:34.375 --> 00:50:35.918
I've seen that painting way back.

00:50:37.162 --> 00:50:38.538
What are you doing here?

00:50:39.480 --> 00:50:40.940
Remember, you told me

00:50:40.940 --> 00:50:42.441
you want to meet my whole family?

00:50:42.799 --> 00:50:45.635
Because you're interested
in learning my family's history.

00:50:46.445 --> 00:50:48.698
- Huh?
- Come, I'll introduce you now.

00:51:05.436 --> 00:51:08.565
Mr. Juanito asked to
be buried in this place.

00:51:09.109 --> 00:51:12.696
Because this is where
he'll wait for his beloved.

00:51:17.779 --> 00:51:19.322
I know everything now, Carmela.

00:51:20.978 --> 00:51:22.062
And I accept...

00:51:23.733 --> 00:51:25.109
That nothing could ever compare

00:51:25.109 --> 00:51:27.028
to your love for Mr. Juanito.

00:51:34.243 --> 00:51:35.494
I'll be going then.

00:51:35.494 --> 00:51:38.664
I might miss my flight to Italy.

00:51:39.373 --> 00:51:41.931
I will be an apprentice
under a chef at his restaurant.

00:51:43.102 --> 00:51:44.145
I'm happy for you.

00:51:44.170 --> 00:51:45.838
You'll get to fulfill your dream.

00:51:46.370 --> 00:51:48.039
I'm also happy for you.

00:51:48.240 --> 00:51:50.867
Future professor. Carmela Isabella.

00:51:53.846 --> 00:51:54.846
Take care.

00:52:25.343 --> 00:52:27.670
August 4,

00:52:28.356 --> 00:52:31.343
1963.

00:52:31.950 --> 00:52:33.389
Carmela, my beloved.

00:52:34.148 --> 00:52:37.869
It pains me whenever
I'm reminded about our situation.

00:52:38.702 --> 00:52:40.224
Because no matter what happens,

00:52:40.850 --> 00:52:42.356
no matter what I do,

00:52:42.794 --> 00:52:46.787
even if I were to stake my life, I know
I would never be able to be with you.

00:52:49.023 --> 00:52:52.277
It was too late when I learned
you weren't from this time.

00:52:53.449 --> 00:52:55.684
And that you were
brought here for a mission.

00:52:58.711 --> 00:53:00.685
Which is to save me from death.

00:53:10.076 --> 00:53:13.836
I learned about your secret
the day I read your letter.

00:53:14.575 --> 00:53:16.843
Where in you said,
you won't be able to come back.

00:53:17.953 --> 00:53:19.092
Along with this...

00:53:19.118 --> 00:53:21.137
Don Alejandro learned that

00:53:21.338 --> 00:53:25.371
there was a rebel that pretended
to be a guard in your home.

00:53:25.919 --> 00:53:27.725
We entered your home,

00:53:27.759 --> 00:53:30.118
to get the letter
I gave to you.

00:53:30.218 --> 00:53:32.826
Where I shared the whole
plan to you.

00:53:33.113 --> 00:53:35.145
So that it wouldn't be
taken in as evidence.

00:53:35.481 --> 00:53:38.907
That's when I saw your diary.

00:53:40.285 --> 00:53:44.636
I remembered you were
always carrying that diary.

00:53:45.040 --> 00:53:46.519
That's why I apologize

00:53:46.842 --> 00:53:49.762
for taking it,
because I wanted to read

00:53:49.992 --> 00:53:51.639
your inner thoughts.

00:53:51.961 --> 00:53:54.160
We learned from Eduardo

00:53:54.566 --> 00:53:59.108
that you and your family were heading
to Spain, along with some officials.

00:54:00.013 --> 00:54:02.340
That's why I followed you.

00:54:03.264 --> 00:54:04.264
Carmela.

00:54:04.403 --> 00:54:05.736
What do you mean, 'Carmela?'

00:54:05.874 --> 00:54:08.480
But I was surprised
when you suddenly pointed a gun at me.

00:54:08.651 --> 00:54:11.210
I also noticed the shift in your emotions.

00:54:11.241 --> 00:54:15.068
That's why I believed
what you wrote on your diary.

00:54:15.152 --> 00:54:17.433
That you're not Carmelita Montecarlos.

00:54:17.500 --> 00:54:19.567
Because you're Carmela Isabella.

00:54:20.284 --> 00:54:22.463
Who is from a different time.

00:54:22.610 --> 00:54:23.861
Don't come near me!

00:54:30.193 --> 00:54:31.194
Juanito...

00:54:35.841 --> 00:54:38.010
Even if you were not born in this era...

00:54:40.554 --> 00:54:42.264
You will still be the one I love.

00:54:47.527 --> 00:54:48.820
I hope I make you smile,

00:54:49.647 --> 00:54:52.024
because I fulfilled
my promise to you.

00:54:53.275 --> 00:54:54.902
I lived for a long time.

00:54:58.113 --> 00:55:00.282
And even though I am not
holding your hand now...

00:55:01.826 --> 00:55:02.868
Know that

00:55:03.118 --> 00:55:05.746
my heart will never let you go.

00:55:06.163 --> 00:55:09.708
Forgive me if I cannot wait for you anymore
at our meeting place.

00:55:12.169 --> 00:55:13.629
But always remember...

00:55:14.922 --> 00:55:17.007
That I love you very much, Carmela.

00:55:23.848 --> 00:55:27.518
This place, where everything
started, is the witness.

00:55:29.144 --> 00:55:31.146
I still love you, Juanito.

00:55:35.025 --> 00:55:36.652
Until we meet again, my beloved.

00:55:38.070 --> 00:55:41.574
With love, Juanito Alfonso.

00:55:48.539 --> 00:55:49.874
Dear Diary,

00:55:49.952 --> 00:55:53.538
thank you very much for everything
that you made me understand.

00:55:54.050 --> 00:55:57.095
Now I know that even if
there's a lot of deserving people,

00:55:57.161 --> 00:55:58.871
I was the chosen one.

00:56:02.386 --> 00:56:05.958
I learned to give importance
to people that surrounds me.

00:56:08.153 --> 00:56:10.881
I also learned to love truly.

00:56:14.523 --> 00:56:15.524
Juanito.

00:56:16.025 --> 00:56:20.525
I will forever cherish
what we have in my heart.

00:56:20.946 --> 00:56:23.616
You will be definitely that
last person I will truly love.

00:56:24.909 --> 00:56:27.161
I am Carmela Isabella,

00:56:27.186 --> 00:56:30.022
a spoiled feisty woman
who is bitter in love.

00:56:30.890 --> 00:56:32.099
But everything

00:56:32.124 --> 00:56:34.001
changed when I went to the

00:56:34.026 --> 00:56:35.736
year 1892.

00:56:45.304 --> 00:56:49.208
The woman in this painting
looks so much like my sister, Carmela.

00:56:49.651 --> 00:56:52.612
But that was painted in 1892.

00:56:53.646 --> 00:56:55.606
That's why it was a big mystery

00:56:55.606 --> 00:56:58.545
why its title became "Carmela Isabella."

00:56:59.071 --> 00:57:00.864
Who are those in the painting to the right?

00:57:01.111 --> 00:57:02.905
That is the Alfonso family.

00:57:03.280 --> 00:57:04.698
The family who were said to be

00:57:04.698 --> 00:57:08.077
the first to settle here in San Alfonso.

00:57:08.869 --> 00:57:11.288
I am Juanito Alfonso VI.

00:57:12.206 --> 00:57:14.875
But you can call me Jun.

00:57:16.126 --> 00:57:17.711
- Grandma!
- Oh, Carmela.

00:57:19.588 --> 00:57:21.757
Mom and I are going to the church.

00:57:21.782 --> 00:57:23.025
Do you want to come?

00:57:23.050 --> 00:57:25.778
Yes, I will come with you
and your Mommy to church.

00:57:25.803 --> 00:57:28.180
But the mass would be later.

00:57:28.205 --> 00:57:30.082
And your mommy is still sleeping.

00:57:30.543 --> 00:57:34.370
So, just play around here for now.

00:57:39.959 --> 00:57:40.964
Dad?

00:57:41.572 --> 00:57:43.832
And who is this

00:57:43.921 --> 00:57:47.257
handsome little gentleman?

00:57:47.282 --> 00:57:48.742
What's your name, child?

00:57:49.172 --> 00:57:50.245
Hey.

00:57:50.330 --> 00:57:51.623
Grandma is asking you.

00:57:51.870 --> 00:57:52.955
What is your name?

00:57:55.474 --> 00:57:56.596
It's Juanito.

00:57:57.167 --> 00:57:58.460
Apologies, grandma.

00:57:58.752 --> 00:58:01.046
This boy's really shy.

00:58:02.381 --> 00:58:04.675
Your child's name is
also Juanito Alfonso?

00:58:05.488 --> 00:58:06.640
Yes, grandmother.

00:58:06.802 --> 00:58:09.529
Juanito Alfonso VII.

00:58:09.680 --> 00:58:11.062
That's his name.

00:58:12.674 --> 00:58:14.286
Fascinating.

00:58:14.937 --> 00:58:15.966
By the way,

00:58:15.991 --> 00:58:19.356
I want to show you
the flowers in the garden.

00:58:19.381 --> 00:58:22.009
My sister Carmela planted those before.

00:58:22.317 --> 00:58:24.068
- Let's go.
- Alright.

00:58:24.181 --> 00:58:26.100
Juanito, you wanna come?

00:58:26.159 --> 00:58:27.494
I'll just stay here.

00:58:27.546 --> 00:58:28.546
Alright.

00:58:29.283 --> 00:58:30.534
Just explore.

00:58:30.559 --> 00:58:33.145
Look at the beautiful paintings.

00:58:34.079 --> 00:58:35.079
Alright then.

00:58:35.581 --> 00:58:36.793
- Let's go.
- Okay.

00:58:37.833 --> 00:58:39.126
Juanito, stay here, okay?

00:59:07.228 --> 00:59:08.228
Who is she?

00:59:08.566 --> 00:59:09.859
I don't know.

00:59:09.907 --> 00:59:11.033
Who are you anyway?

00:59:11.967 --> 00:59:14.682
My name is Juanito Alfonso VII.

00:59:14.798 --> 00:59:16.800
I will complain about you to my Dad

00:59:16.825 --> 00:59:18.105
because you're being mean to me.

00:59:18.557 --> 00:59:20.017
Then complain about me!

00:59:20.042 --> 00:59:23.131
I will also complain about
you to my Mom and Grandma.

00:59:23.921 --> 00:59:24.921
Carmela?

00:59:25.464 --> 00:59:26.965
Carmela's your name?

00:59:27.299 --> 00:59:30.094
Your name's so pretty.
It suits you.

00:59:30.479 --> 00:59:32.261
Too bad you're being mean.

00:59:32.286 --> 00:59:34.984
I didn't even do anything wrong.

00:59:36.433 --> 00:59:38.310
I have a secret to tell you.

00:59:38.644 --> 00:59:39.930
I have a third eye.

00:59:40.979 --> 00:59:42.856
It's true.
Come, quickly.

00:59:47.361 --> 00:59:48.361
Look at this.

00:59:48.403 --> 00:59:50.339
I'm the only one who can see

00:59:50.364 --> 00:59:52.212
and read what's inside.

00:59:52.673 --> 00:59:55.176
I told my Mom and Grandma about it,

00:59:55.285 --> 00:59:57.615
but they both can't read it.

00:59:58.055 --> 00:59:59.932
I'm the only one who can read it,

00:59:59.957 --> 01:00:02.042
which means,
my third eye's open.

01:00:15.848 --> 01:00:17.391
I can also read it.

01:00:17.724 --> 01:00:19.595
Really? What's written on it then?

01:00:20.853 --> 01:00:21.853
It says...

01:00:23.730 --> 01:00:25.065
Wow, that's cool!

01:00:25.090 --> 01:00:27.217
Both of our third eyes are open!

01:00:28.443 --> 01:00:29.603
What's that supposed to mean?

01:00:29.903 --> 01:00:32.281
This is the sign for
being happy and okay.

01:00:34.428 --> 01:00:35.450
Let's go outside.

01:00:35.450 --> 01:00:36.827
Maybe this isn't allowed.

01:00:36.852 --> 01:00:38.862
We might get reprimanded.